frontmatter.title: A System for Automatic Calculation of the Eye-Voice Span

node.html: A system to predict the level of english of a reader by analysing the movement of eye gaze and the phonetics (voice). Introduced a new approach to compute the eye voice span.

frontmatter.title: Text classification of BBC news dataset

node.html: This project is about text classification ie: given a text, we would want to predict its class (tech, business, sport, entertainment or politics), We compered perfomence of different models and visualize word embedding in 2D and 3D.
Detection of questions on Quora, and classification of insincere questions user tensorflow hub.
In this project, we built a Face Mask Detector using Keras, Tensorflow, MobileNet and OpenCV.
A simple Google Keep clone built with Vue and Firebase.
Custom WordPress theme and e-commerce site built with Timber and WooCommerce for blistabloc, a start-up selling the only reactive shoe insert that prevents blisters from forming.
A minimal, dark blue theme for VS Code, Sublime Text, Atom, iTerm, and more. Available on Visual Studio Marketplace, Package Control, Atom Package Manager, and npm.

frontmatter.title: Apple Music Embeddable Web Player Widget

node.html: Embeddable web player widget for Apple Music that lets users log in and listen to full song playback in the browser leveraging MusicKit.js. Read more about this project on 9to5Mac.
Interactive marketing website for Northeastern's first annual student-led design conference, Interventions.

Student web portal prototype built after conducting multiple rounds of user testing that aimed to improve the current portal to provide students at Northeastern University with a better user experience.
Web application built on the MEAN (MongoDB, Express, Angular, Node) stack with the intention of providing Northeastern students a better experience browsing the courses offered at Northeastern.
Interactive holiday site for MullenLowe built around an algorithm that generated a holiday greeting to each and every person on the planet. Check out this short video describing the project.
